channel.title: Fuck! I think I fried my computer
channel.description: Well, Me being a dumb ass.. I think I friend my computer... well, I went to put more ram in, and I put it in backwards.. and turned it on (I didnt know I put in backwards it went in rather easy).. Well my computer cut on and cut off and now won't turn back on... This is a emachine t2892 (You can replace parts in this model). Uhm, Well. if I fried something what is it.. and how or what part will I need... (I dont want to get a new computer)

item.title: Fuck! I think I fried my computer
item.dc:creator: @T41 t4
item.description:
@T41 wrote:

Original Daniel:

Any computer made in the last 6+ years won’t let you install ram backwards. You might have not pushed it in all the way.

QFT

Also, I doubt it was that. You could have unhooked your HDD PSU cable slightly to cut-off, or you need to reset CMOS. Try taking the RAM out, completely powering down (turn off PSU) and try to power on.
